transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yes, I received an order, I had made an initial order, give me your zip code so I can check.

Speaker 2: It’s 93004, and what's your first and last name?

Speaker 1: Roger, KIDA, K-I-D-A, and what's—

Speaker 2: All right, and are you referring to the refill that came out, or what's going on?

Speaker 1: Yeah, which I don't want any refills unless I order them.

Speaker 2: We can set it up that way, that's fine.

Speaker 1: So basically in the next five months, we won't ship you anything for the next—

Speaker 2: Five months, you'll have to call us for your next order.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, I'll have to call you, I won't receive any more unsolicited, or anything—

Speaker 2: That I haven't ordered, correct?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so you could have chosen this option from your first purchase, not sure why you—

Speaker 2: Didn't, but right now we're going to set it up so you can choose your next order in the—

Speaker 1: Next five months.

Speaker 2: I never want this with any company, so if I had seen an option to not do this, I would—

Speaker 1: Because I hate when they keep sending you stuff, and you don't need it or want it.

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: And now I'm being charged for this order, I'm assuming?

Speaker 2: I'm sure I am.

Speaker 1: Well, you had an order shipped out on the 19th, that was a few days ago, so yeah, that's—

Speaker 2: Already been delivered, it says, actually.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, that's great.

Speaker 2: Well, no more.

Speaker 1: So do you want no more, or do you want to order as needed?

Speaker 2: I'm confused.

Speaker 1: Well, I mean, as long as they're not sent to me, without me placing the order, I'm fine—

Speaker 2: To have an account, but I don't want anything unless I order them.

Speaker 1: Yeah, but your account doesn't last forever, so your prescription lasts, like I said, well—

Speaker 2: I'll hold it for five months and let you order your next refills in that time, but it does—

Speaker 1: Not last forever.

Speaker 2: Well, then I'll cancel my account now.

Speaker 1: Amazing, okay, we'll cancel you out then, you're all canceled.

Speaker 2: I'll just redo the account.

Speaker 1: Once we cancel your prescription, you're not going to be able to reorder, sir, even if—

Speaker 2: You change your mind.

Speaker 1: So tell me, what does five months mean?

Speaker 2: Tell me about that.

Speaker 1: Your prescription doesn't last forever, so it only usually lasts about a year, so generally—

Speaker 2: We will put it on hold for five or six months, let the customer call for his orders in that—

Speaker 1: Time, when they call in, we can push it out five or six months from the day they call—

Speaker 2: And then they can call again when they want, but you can't cancel your prescription and—

Speaker 1: Then try to call and get refills because you don't have a prescription anymore, so there's—

Speaker 2: No refills to get.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I understand.

Speaker 2: And then renewing multiple prescriptions just because someone wants to cancel after every—

Speaker 1: Order is just very inefficient for the company.

Speaker 2: So if you want to hold or pause or whatever the case is, we can help you, we can oblige—

Speaker 1: But if you just want to cancel, then we can do that too, but we can't just have someone—

Speaker 2: Redo multiple prescriptions.

Speaker 1: Well, I don't mind hold, yeah, I understand your explanation.

Speaker 2: As long as they don't send me anything else, unless I order it, that's all I want to make—

Speaker 1: Of it.

Speaker 2: Okay, if you'd like, I can give you my name and extension, you can put your next order—

Speaker 1: In with me and I can make sure that your account stays like this.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's fine.

Speaker 1: All right, so there's just simply the same number, oh no, not the same number, it's going—

Speaker 2: To be 800-675.

Speaker 1: Yeah, 5807 or 9807.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's what's on the top of the line.

Speaker 1: All right, and then just put my extension as 0035.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: You're welcome, sir.

Speaker 2: All right, have a great day.

Speaker 1: Bye now.

Speaker 2: Bye.
